snippet.textDisplay: As much as I think this is the song of this season and appreciate coke studio for introducing me to this song... I just wish it were lil toned down, the musical structure was overpacked. It started magnificently with ali hamza's vocal wish he continued the whole song without the whole shazam.. It could easily would've been a magical one if were along the lines of simple strings and ali's vocal alone. I know fusion is the forte of the format but no need to stretch it. Just thinking if this given treatment of hor vi neevan, it would've been gold. Frankly speaking am listening only till ali's part end and looping it back. And that's a shame. PS : not disrespecting. Just what I would've preferred

snippet.textDisplay: It's about conversation between Sohni and her clay pot, which is about to sink along her. She used to travel across river Chenab each night to meet mahiwal, but one day that clay pot replaced with the one having unbaked clay by her sister-in-law, so in middle of river she realized it's not her pot and she won't be able to cross the river to meet mahiwal. snippet.textDisplay:
Par Chana de, has to be the most beautiful folk song, ever on Coke studio.....I keep listening to it non-stop, it is so melodious and heart-wrenching, the voices are superb, the music is fantastic, the lyrics based on a folk romance, sohni manhiwaal, is stupendously heartwarming, the music Direction by NOORI is absolutely FANTASTIC!!!!!!!! A very very very very well composed rendition, kudos to the whole team and I am pleased to say that there is absolutely no dearth of TALENT in our country....with such memorable romances, how can the creative genius not be able to construct such a tremendous feat......BRAVO BRAVO BRAVO.....
THIS NEEDS SO MANY STANDING OVATIONS ❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️
